commit_list.message: Added svn:ignore *.log to the log directory, added a 'requires.rb' initializer for putting all the requires in the same place (I think it reduces memory when under mod_rails if you load libraries up front), added timeout and socketerror rescues to RollsController#create so if snipr or net connection is down you get a meaningful error message, changed eval() to send() in RollsController#create (to avoid people being able to hack the site with  params[:expire_data_num] = '10.times { exec(something evil) }'), changed link in RailsController#create from http://rickroll.tv/rolls/show/1 to roll_url(@roll) (same link, but now works in development mode too), added a rolliness validate method to the roll model (making sure that the user selected some kind of misdirection technique), changed the URL_REGEX to URI::Regexp (the old regex didn't accept http://rickroll.tv/ as a valid url.. weird.  I would have fixed it, but it was over my head.  Luckily the URI class has that regex method that generates one for you.), changed the pulldown box on the front page from a max of 31 to 60 (it was making me sad that I couldn't do 45 minutes.)  Wish I had done some sort of substantial cool new feature, but creativity is running dry today.  Maybe after a few beers...
